{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3557cfd2-247b-4500-b1c3-928b9806398f","content":"Yes, you'll have compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+ and .NET Framework 4.6.2+**, but it **dropped support for**:\n\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — End-of-life; not supported in MSTest v3.\n- **`net5.0`** — End-of-life; not supported in MSTest v3.\n\nYour `net462` target is fine (meets the .NET Framework 4.6.2 minimum).\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n1. Replace `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` with a supported target like `net6.0` or `net8.0`.\n2. Update the package references to MSTest v3 (e.g., `3.x` versions or switch to the unified `MSTest` meta-package).\n\nAlso review any use of deprecated APIs — MSTest v3 removed some older attributes and changed some default behaviors (e.g., test parallelization defaults). Would you like me to perform the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2aa37c66-142c-471a-a650-a792eba94ecf","outputTokens":248,"requestId":"2409:B6F84:48D7F5:4DFADA:6A03112F"},"id":"f07251fc-9485-413d-a3ca-d7df64eda9f9","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:38:32.543Z","parentId":"582aea39-eca5-4f65-ae8d-2f4104a3db0d"}
